{
  "texts": [
    "The four features identified in this dimension are: a) read only -no direct involvement is possible; users can only communicate to the catalogue via read-only user interface, API or other mechanism such as email or feedback form; b) read and write -curators and developers can use services to get information from the catalogue and be directly involved through the creation of their records to be added to the catalogue and increase their visibility; c) 3rd party -community features delegated to 3rd party tool or platform, e.g.",
    "GitHub issues; d) suggestion -a dedicated page for content suggestion (e.g.",
    "term change and term proposal) is available.",
    "Sustainability (Su).",
    "The models to sustain services financially and preserve the catalogue in the long run that are in place."
  ]
}